Data Analysis/Data Visualization Report: Bike Ride Trends and Biker Types of Ford GoBike System April, 2019¶

by (Nisreen ALassa)¶

Investigation Overview¶

In this investigation, I will explore bike ride trends and biker types of the Bay Area bike share system. The main focus is on biking duration, time patterns (weekday and hour), and bike types.

Dataset Overview and Executive Summary¶

This document analyzes Ford GoBike's trip data for April FY2019. Attributes include trip start/end times, user type, gender, and age. 16K data points were excluded due to missing values, data inconsistencies, or outlier issues.

Bike Ride Duration Time Visualization:¶

The original duration data is right-skewed with durations ranging from less than 1 minute to 1400+ minutes.

The median is around 9 minutes, and the mean is around 12 minutes.

Analysis of Bike Ride Duration and Member Age Across Categorical Features:¶

Investigated Features: Member Gender, User Type, Start Time Day of Week, Start Time Hour:

Observations:

  • Ride duration (in minutes) exhibits significant variation across different user types and member genders.
  • Subscribers tend to have shorter rides compared to Customers, likely due to their higher frequency of rides during peak hours.
  • Customers, on the other hand, seem to take longer rides, especially during weekends and non-peak hours.
  • Member age also influences ride duration. Older members tend to ride for longer periods compared to younger members, regardless of the time of day or day of the week.
  • Gender differences in ride duration are apparent. Male riders tend to take shorter rides compared to female riders, with the latter showing longer durations, especially during weekends.
<Figure size 1500x1500 with 0 Axes>

Bike Ride Durations for Different Age Groups¶

Observations:

  • Younger bikers (<40 years old) are more frequent across all days and times. However, their ride durations tend to be shorter compared to older bikers.
  • Older bikers (>=40 years old) generally have longer ride durations, particularly on weekends.
  • Weekend rides are associated with longer durations, especially during late mornings and afternoons (e.g., 10:00 AM to 2:00 PM).
  • Customer users tend to have longer ride durations, particularly on weekends, while subscriber users typically have shorter rides, especially during weekdays.
  • Ride durations increase with age, with older bikers consistently riding for longer periods across different days and times.
  • The highest ride durations are seen on weekends, particularly for older bikers and customer users.
